---
description: Enforce section-based CMS component architecture for TypeScript files
globs: **/*.{ts,tsx}
alwaysApply: false
---

# CMS Section Architecture

- Build the CMS as a single admin page composed of ordered sections:
  1. Environment Connection, 2) Articles, 3) Content Editor + Preview.
- Each section must be a dedicated component folder, not inline in the page.
- Minimum files per section component:
  - `SectionName.tsx`
  - `styles.ts`
- Keep section concerns isolated: connection logic in connection section, article selection in articles section, editing logic in content section.
- The page file should orchestrate state and section composition only; avoid large UI logic blocks in the page.
- Use MUI layout primitives and `Paper` as the base visual container per section.
- If requested behavior conflicts with this structure, ask for confirmation before deviating.

# Expected Pattern

```tsx
// sections/ConnectionSection/ConnectionSection.tsx
// sections/ConnectionSection/styles.ts
// sections/ArticlesSection/ArticlesSection.tsx
// sections/ArticlesSection/styles.ts
// sections/ContentSection/ContentSection.tsx
// sections/ContentSection/styles.ts
```
